# =============================================================================
# sqip — Tobias Baldauf + Axel Jurada Schäfer (axe312ger)'s
#         "SVG-based LQIP (Low Quality Image Placeholder)
#         technique" — a Node.js CLI that generates COMPACT
#         SVG-based placeholder images from JPEG/PNG/WebP
#         source images.  Distinct from inline base64-PNG
#         placeholders by producing vector-based SVG
#         placeholders (typically 600-800 bytes each) that:
#           - Use Michael Fogleman's "primitive" algorithm
#             (geometric primitive reconstruction via simulated
#             annealing) to generate the image shape from a
#             small set of triangles/rectangles/circles/etc
#           - Blur the SVG with a Gaussian filter for visual
#             smoothness
#           - Optionally include the original image's average
#             color as a base layer
#           - Compress to base64-encoded data: URIs for inline
#             HTML embedding
#         Used as the LQIP layer in performance-conscious web
#         frameworks: Gatsby, Next.js Image, Astro, Vite, etc.
#         Pioneered by Tobias Baldauf in 2017 as an alternative
#         to base64-PNG placeholders (which are typically 4-8 KB
#         vs SQIP's 600-800 bytes).  SQIP is pronounced "skwib"
#         (Harry Potter's term for a non-magical person of
#         magical descent).
#
# Author:  Tobias Baldauf (original concept) + Axel Jurada
#          Schäfer (axe312ger, current maintainer) + community
#          contributors.  axe312ger has maintained the SQIP
#          monorepo since ~2018 with regular updates.
# Source:  https://github.com/axe312ger/sqip
#          https://github.com/axe312ger/sqip/blob/main/packages/sqip-cli/src/sqip-cli.ts
# CLI:     packages/sqip-cli/src/sqip-cli.ts — uses
#          `command-line-args` (already documented R561 _pyret)
#          for argv parsing + `command-line-usage` for help
#          output.  Headline observability library: TJ
#          Holowaychuk's `debug` module for namespace-filtered
#          debug logging throughout the SQIP pipeline.
# Library: debug (TJ Holowaychuk / debug-js)
#          ("A tiny JavaScript debugging utility modelled after
#           Node.js core's debugging technique. Works in Node.js
#           and web browsers." — TJ Holowaychuk + debug-js team
#           — released 2011 as one of the FOUNDATIONAL Node.js
#           libraries by TJ (also creator of Express.js,
#           commander.js, mocha, jade/pug, koa, stylus, n
#           Node version manager).
#           debug introduced the `DEBUG=namespace:*` environment
#           variable pattern that became standard across the
#           Node ecosystem AND influenced Rust's RUST_LOG
#           syntax (env_logger R582) by ~10 years.  Uses
#           NAMESPACE-BASED FILTERING (not level-based):
#           every `debug('namespace')(...)` call belongs to
#           a namespace; `DEBUG=express:* npm start` enables
#           all Express namespaces; `DEBUG=*` enables all.)
# License: AGPL-3.0 (SQIP); MIT (debug)
# Status:  sqip — 3409+ stars on axe312ger/sqip, periodic
#          maintenance; debug — 11200+ stars on debug-js/debug
#          (top-50 Node module by stars), 1.7B+ weekly npm
#          downloads, foundational dependency of Express +
#          Mocha + Socket.io + Body-parser + Send + Connect +
#          Cookie + Mongoose + Sequelize + tens of thousands
#          of other npm packages (one of the most-downloaded
